{"TopicId":113622,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Piggy-Back Fail (First Fraps Test)","CreatedByName":"ace.1991","CreatedById":57829,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-06-21T17:53:56Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"ace.1991","CreatedById":57829,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-06-21T17:53:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EMy first time using fraps in KSP \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E Woot!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDecided to test a piggy-backed space plane prototype I\u0027ve been toying with lately. This is the second in-flight seperation test, and it...doesn\u0027t end well.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEnjoy \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022480\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/sxCh-vOn8lw?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MaverickSawyer","CreatedById":11952,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-06-21T23:30:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ace.1991\u0022 data-cite=\u0022ace.1991\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EMy first time using fraps in KSP \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E Woot!\u003Cp\u003EDecided to test a piggy-backed space plane prototype I\u0027ve been toying with lately. This is the second in-flight seperation test, and it...doesn\u0027t end well.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEnjoy \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022480\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/sxCh-vOn8lw?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAh.... I see the problem(s)...\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E1. You need to have some form of forward thrust to keep the smaller aircraft from hitting the tail.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E2. You need more upward force to help clear the carrier aircraft in a timely fashion.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mike9606","CreatedById":90275,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-06-21T23:36:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EAn H-tail or something similar may have worked better than the standard tail setup in that situation.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ace.1991","CreatedById":57829,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-06-21T23:57:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EActually, it turned out the problem was that I\u0027d disabled the payloads control surfaces and set the engine to 0%... then forgot i did all of that \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_embarrassed.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:blush:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn my defence, it worked perfectly the first time i flew it. but that was a while ago.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}